Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle with the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet},
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%milliliters},
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Toss the tomatoes through the dressing, then set aside.

When the fries have 10-12 mins remaining, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high
heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, fry the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} until browned,
~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

When the burgers are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Carefully place the
cheese on top of the burgers.

Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}), then set aside, off the heat, to allow the
cheese to melt, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Just before everything's ready, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop into the oven to
warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{40%grams} leaves to the bowl of tomatoes
and dressing. Toss to coat in the dressing.

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun bases and
@sweet chilli sauce{32%grams} over the lids.

Top the bases with the cheesy plant-based burgers and some of the dressed rocket
leaves, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve your burgers with the seasoned fries and remaining salad on the side.
Enjoy!